      "comment": "DAZZLING GEISHA (6) came from a long way back when beaten 1.5L at Mackay on debut and then tacked the $151,000 QTIS 2yo Plate here and found that a stretch too far. Finally draws a low gate and is likely to settle a lot closer. In the premier local stable, this is winnable with the extra fitness. SPORT (3) resumed against the above at Mackay, bet into $2.4 favouritism, missing by 2L. Was beaten 1L this track/trip, following and will be better for that. Has winning claims. STYLISH DIAMOND (5) resumed improved, narrowly beaten in an Open 2 at Mackay. Comes back home, and she has claims with the extra fitness, positioning forward. FORMAL AFFAIR (7) raced at Ipswich on debut over a short course and she was in the market. Draws inside and can improve over the longer sprint. THE BARBER (2) debuts with the blinkers on, and his latest trial here was good. A betting watch.",
